    majorExports: "Starship repairs, forged documents, information",
    majorImports: "Starship parts, various trade goods between visiting spacers",
    source: "WEG40217 Platt's Starport Guide p.80",
    summary: "Omze's Incredible Traveling Starport is a former Rendili StarDrive Neutron Star Bulk Cruiser (the Allanthia, 600 meters) refitted with docking bays and starship facilities. Run by an eccentric old Sludir named Omze, the starport jumps from system to system, mostly throughout the Outer Rim and Mid Rim, providing services in systems with limited ports. It serves light freighters in three main docking bays (four per bay), with external gantries for passenger access and belly couplers for larger vessels. The starport fosters a carnival-like sideshow atmosphere where free-traders hawk cargoes, technicians holler deals on repairs, and a copious mix of aliens creates the busiest circus this side of Coruscant. It stays in systems from a week to a few months on an unpredictable schedule.",
    locations: "Docking Bays (3 main bays, 4 light freighters each; one dedicated repair bay with gantry cranes, heavy equipment, and huge parts inventory including illegal sensor systems). External Docking Gantries (swing and lock flush for hyperspace transit; 50–75 cr docking fee). Belly Docking Couplers (2 medium transports or 1 bulk freighter). Con'varra's Datawork Central (forged documents — IDs, licenses, weapons permits; 2,500–5,000 cr each, up to 5 days). General Quarters (luxury suites at 75 cr/night, 50 cr meals; run by Brobius the Bith steward; rumored secret passages used to kidnap Human guests). Futor's Network (infochant office — commerce stats, bounty listings, Imperial shipping data; 200–2,000 cr per tidbit; eavesdropping devices throughout the starport). Starboard Broadside Club (bar/gambling hall along starboard viewports; run by Broadside the Wookiee; Twi'lek serving girls; gaming tables; live band; bugged with listening devices). Bridge/Command Center (off-limits, heavily guarded; Omze's luxury cabin nearby). Secure Cargo Holds (rumored treasure vault, off-limits).",
    ofNote: "Docking fees: 100 cr/day (up to 150 cr for Humans — Omze's anti-Human bias). Gantry docking: 50–75 cr. Hyperspace transport fee for hitchhikers: up to 1,500 cr. Repairs/modifications: 150–200% normal cost but far superior quality and durability. No customs authority but casual cargo monitoring. All-alien crew — no Humans employed. Rodian mercenary company (led by Ne'Chak) provides security with blatant anti-Human bias. Rules: no brawls, no blaster fights, no cheating at gambling, no swindling cargo deals, no crass comments about aliens — penalty is immediate expulsion regardless of ship readiness. Omze keeps records of all ship modifications (potentially sold to bounty hunters/Imperials). Omze does not personally trade in cargoes, but spacers actively trade among themselves in the docking bays. Notable NPCs (see Notable NPC Lookup on NPC tab): Omze (Sludir owner/operator), Ne'Chak (Rodian mercenary captain), Golben (Jillsarian chief technician), Con'varra (Twi'lek master forger), Futor (Sullustan infochant/slicer), Broadside (Wookiee bartender/enforcer), Brobius (Bith steward), Lady Felsing (Wroonian con artist), plus Rodian Security Mercenaries and Omze's Technicians."
