    techLevel: "Industrial",
    majorExports: "Ryll, slaves",
    majorImports: "Mid and high technology",
    source: "WEG40217 Platt's Starport Guide p.136",
    summary: "Ryloth is the inhospitable Twi'lek homeworld, a tidally locked planet of twisted rock formations and mountains. The sun-baked day side — called the Bright Lands by Twi'leks — is perpetually scorched and uninhabitable. The dark side is kept barely warm enough for life by heat storms: powerful blasts of superheated air from the Bright Lands that blast through canyons and mountain ranges at up to 500 km/h, tossing starships like leaves. Lifeforms survive by sheltering in deep caves during storms. Several Twi'lek cities exist just beneath the surface, either carved into rocky terrain or built to blend with it. Each city is autonomous and governed by a five-member head-clan, each member overseeing one major aspect of city life: production, agriculture, power, air and water, and starport services. Because Twi'leks have long been prey to slavers who demand annual tribute, they do not broadcast their cities' locations with starport beacons or guidance markers.",
    locations: "Kala'uun (city within the Lonely Five rock formation near the terminus; limited starport services, ryll trade — see Kala'uun entry). The Lonely Five (cluster of five immense basalt rock formations near the terminus; contains Kala'uun). The Bright Lands (the scorching day side; a barren, lethal wasteland). The Terminus (constant boundary between the Bright Lands and the dark side; Twi'lek cities cluster along this zone).",
    ofNote: "Navigation hazard: heat storms scour Ryloth's lower atmosphere with superheated gusts up to 500 km/h — unpredictable and deadly to ships flying at low altitude. Sensors can detect a slow temperature rise at the leading edge of a storm (Easy sensors roll); pilots have about one minute to react. Pilots searching for hidden Twi'lek cities should fly along the terminus at high altitude above the peaks; drop into lower altitudes only when certain of approach. If caught in a heat storm: Very Difficult space transports or starfighter piloting to maintain control at altitude (add ship's maneuverability); Heroic if flying low through canyons. Pull up above the storm to safer atmosphere when possible. Twi'lek cities are hostile to outsiders and do not advertise their locations."
