    lengthOfDay: "23 standard hours",
    lengthOfYear: "341 local days",
    sapientSpecies: "None",
    starport: "None",
    population: "None",
    function: "Unexplored",
    government: "None",
    techLevel: "None",
    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "None",
    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.470",
    summary: "Dagobah sits in the Sluis sector not far from the Rimma Trade Route, but its location was deliberately obscured — the planet was erased from Jedi Archives and does not appear on standard star charts, reachable only via obscure hyperspace traces. Its perpetually shadowed surface is covered by a dense, steaming swamp canopy hiding an eat-or-be-eaten ecosystem. Life ranges from microscopic silverfish to colossal vacuum-feeding swamp slugs. Notable creatures include sharp-clawed dragonsnakes, airborne bogwings, and gnarltrees — spider-like predators that calcify into immobile root systems as they age. A dark side cave — the residual Force energy of a Dark Jedi from nearby Bpfassh — permeates one area of the planet, producing unsettling visions and counterbalancing Force signatures. Jedi Master Yoda chose Dagobah as his place of exile in 19 BBY after failing to kill Emperor Palpatine, living in a simple mud hut for over two decades. He trained Luke Skywalker here in 3 ABY before dying in 4 ABY at the age of nine hundred. An attempt to establish a military intelligence outpost here after the Battle of Endor failed quickly. Dagobah has since become a pilgrimage site for students of the new Jedi Order, who seek the dark side cave for Force-inspired vision quests.",
    locations: "Yoda's Hut (simple mud dwelling in the swamp; Yoda's home from 19 BBY to 4 ABY). The Dark Side Cave (a cave permeated by dark side energy — residual signature of a long-dead Dark Jedi from Bpfassh; produces Force visions; used by Jedi pilgrims for vision quests).",
    ofNote: "Dagobah was deliberately removed from Jedi Archives — one of 38 systems Yoda noted had been dropped from the records. No starport, no facilities, no population. Landing in the swamp is treacherous; ships sink into the bog quickly without repulsorlift support. The dark side cave suppresses Force signatures, which is why Yoda could hide here undetected by the Emperor for 23 years. Any Force-sensitive character entering the cave should expect a confrontation with their own dark side potential. Planet is useless to most campaigns except as Yoda's location (pre-4 ABY) or a Jedi pilgrimage site."
