    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.471",
    summary: "Geonosis is a harsh, radiation-scoured desert world neighboring Tatooine in the Arkanis sector. The Geonosians — insectoid hive-dwellers — first encountered outsiders when Tatooine was settled by miners four millennia before the Battle of Yavin. Fascinated by offworld technology, the hives became expert engineers, producing cheap, reliable labor droids in their own image. Contact with outsiders eventually caused deep rifts between the hives, erupting into savage warfare that isolated the planet for centuries. When the Republic rediscovered Geonosis, the hive wars had ebbed; the Geonosians struck a distribution deal with the Baktoid Armor Workshop and returned to the galactic market. Darth Sidious engineered the rise of the Geonosian rebel Poggle the Lesser and used the planet's Trade Federation connections to commission an army of battle droids — and to begin early planning for the Death Star. In 22 BBY Geonosis hosted Count Dooku's meeting with the Separatist leadership, triggering the opening battle of the Clone Wars when Yoda led clone troops from Kamino to rescue captured Jedi. The Republic occupied Geonosis and nationalized its droid output. The Empire maintained tight control, using Geonosian scientists on the Death Star project. The New Republic permitted subcontracting again, with a right of refusal on all projects.",
    locations: "Stalgasin Hive (seat of Poggle the Lesser; major Geonosian hive complex). Petranaki Arena (execution arena used during the opening battle of the Clone Wars; where Anakin, Obi-Wan, and Padmé were nearly executed). Droid Foundries (vast subterranean manufacturing complexes producing battle droids and other war machines).",
    ofNote: "Geonosis neighbors Tatooine at grid R-16 — the two worlds are among the closest inhabited planets in their sector. The planet's rings and arid terrain are distinctive on approach. Clone Wars-era campaigns will find Geonosis an active Separatist manufacturing hub; post-Clone Wars and Imperial-era campaigns should treat droid foundries as nationalized Imperial assets. The Battle of Geonosis (22 BBY) was the first battle of the Clone Wars and the first large-scale lightsaber combat seen in generations."
