    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.471",
    summary: "Kamino orbits a star above the galactic disk, loosely grouped with other fringe stars at the lower periphery of the Ri-shi Maze — it is technically outside the galaxy. The long-necked, graceful Kaminoans evolved from sleek-skinned mammals on a world that once had continents. Around 19,000 BBY, abrupt climate change melted Kamino's glaciers and submerged every landmass under hundreds of meters of seawater, including the parapet city of Derem and the legendary Clock Spires of Harai Nova. The Kaminoans survived by developing stilt cities and mastering cloning science, using it first to preserve drowned species and then to engineer themselves toward genetic perfection. By 4,500 BBY the Republic had discovered Kamino's superior cloning technology, and Tipoca City became the galaxy's premier cloning facility. In 32 BBY Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas commissioned a clone army for the Republic — a project guided to completion by Darth Sidious, who also arranged Kamino's deletion from all stellar databases. The resulting army was the foundation of the Clone Wars (22–19 BBY). The Empire converted Kamino into a fortified stormtrooper production world; in 12 BBY a clone uprising engineered by disgruntled Kaminoan clonemasters was crushed by the 501st Legion. The Empire's collapse in 4 ABY ended mass clone production, and Kamino now survives on smaller contracts — often for warlords and criminal organizations.",
    locations: "Tipoca City (primary Kaminoan stilt city; location of the main cloning facilities and Prime Minister Lama Su's offices). Derem (ancient Kaminoan coastal city; submerged ~19,000 BBY; now an underwater ruin).",
    ofNote: "Kamino does not appear on standard star charts — deliberately deleted from Republic and Imperial databases by Darth Sidious to protect the clone army project. Finding Kamino requires the original Jedi commission records or following gravitational traces from nearby stars (as Obi-Wan Kenobi did in 22 BBY). Kamino's cloning technology is the most advanced in the known galaxy; the Kaminoans will clone anything for the right price, though they maintain strict quality standards. Post-Empire: cloning services available to any buyer with sufficient credits."
