    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.473",
    summary: "Tatooine is a vast yellow desert world orbiting twin suns in the Outer Rim, so hot at midday that early explorers mistook it for a star. Despite its inhospitable conditions, the planet sits at the intersection of two major hyperspace routes — the Triellus Trade Route connecting Hutt Space to the Outer Rim, and a loop of the Corellian Run connecting to the Core — making its spaceports commercially significant. The Jawas, hooded rodent-like scavengers, scour the wastes for salvage. The Tusken Raiders are nomadic desert warriors living by ancient tribal codes. The planet's sparse megafauna includes eopies rooting for buried lichen, rock warts, and the semi-legendary krayt dragon. Tatooine has been settled and abandoned multiple times; current civilization dates to around 700 BBY, when the B'omarr monks established themselves in the planet's desolation. Miners arrived around 100 BBY, mostly becoming moisture farmers. Around 65 BBY the Hutts took formal control, using the planet as a transfer point for smuggled goods. Jabba the Hutt ruled Tatooine's criminal infrastructure until his death shortly before the Battle of Endor. Various crime lords squabbled over the planet until the Hutts returned to reclaim it after the Yuuzhan Vong devastated parts of Hutt Space.",
    locations: "Mos Eisley (largest spaceport city; 'wretched hive of scum and villainy'; home to the Mos Eisley Cantina). Anchorhead (smaller settlement; moisture farmer community). Beggar's Canyon (canyon terrain popular with swoop and skyhopper pilots). Jabba's Palace (B'omarr monastery converted by Jabba the Hutt; located in the Dune Sea). Mos Espa (pod-racing town; site of Anakin Skywalker's childhood home and Watto's shop).",
    ofNote: "The most famous backwater in the galaxy — birthplace of Anakin Skywalker and the world where R2-D2 and C-3PO were found by Luke Skywalker, triggering the events of the Galactic Civil War. Mos Eisley Spaceport is a practical haven for smugglers and criminals; the local Imperial presence is minimal and easily bribed. Hutt law supersedes Imperial authority in practice. Any significant commercial activity requires Hutt approval or willingness to operate covertly. Moisture farming is the primary legitimate occupation; water is Tatooine's most valuable natural commodity. The Dune Sea and Jundland Wastes are extremely dangerous — Tusken Raiders, dragonsnakes, and worse."
